# Electronics Design Workflow

## Circuit Design

Electronic circuits are typically designed using schematic diagrams that represent components and their connections.

Common components include:

• resistors  
• capacitors  
• inductors  
• transistors  
• voltage sources  

## Simulation

Circuit simulation allows engineers to test designs before building physical hardware.

Simulation tools analyze:

- voltage levels
- current flow
- signal behavior
- power consumption

## Electronic Design Automation

EDA software is used to assist with:

• schematic capture  
• circuit simulation  
• PCB layout  
• signal integrity analysis
